                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.0031/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-19T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 19, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 19—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>319. I delivered the memorandum contained in the Department’s 214, June 18, 6
                    p.m., to the Foreign Secretary this afternoon. He said he wished to continue to
                    handle this matter personally after his return from Geneva. He leaves London
                    probably Wednesday of next week.</p>
                <p>I shall see Chamberlain on Wednesday of next week and take occasion to draw his
                    attention to this latest memorandum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
